title: Led Zeppelin - 1970.01.09 Royal Albert Hall (Remaster)
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1970.01.09 Royal Albert Hall (Remaster)   

Led Zeppelin
Royal Albert Hall
London, England
January 9th 1970
SBD
 
SBD - All songs are from the Shirley Pre DVD multi-tracks but have 
been Remastered. 

Added inbetween chatter filler using Cosmic Energy Video audio 
and EVSD "Jimmy's Birthday Party" to make it complete as possible.

CD 1 

1. We're Gonna Groove
2. I Can't Quit You Baby  
3. Dazed And Confused	
4. Heartbreaker
5. White Summer - Black Mountain Side
6. What Is And What Should Never Be
7. Moby Dick

CD 2 

1. How Many More Times
2. Bring It On Home
3. Whole Lotta Love
4. Communication Breakdown
5. C'mon Everybody
6. Something Else
7. Long Tall Sally

Comments: 
This show needs no recommendation. Playing is so hot and the band firing on all 
cylinders tonight ... it's Jimmy's 26th birthday party! Gutsy show with totally 
mind blowing energy. From the first notes of We're Gonna Groove up to the last 
hints of Long Tall Sally this concert is just exceptional. During one of the 
verse on Dazed And Confused Plant changes the lyrics and sings: "This cocaine 
makes me sick!" Amazing!
